{
  "info": {
    "name": "Allocate.AI API Collection",
    "description": "Complete API collection for testing Allocate.AI backend\n\nBase URL: http://localhost:8002\nSession Token: my-test-session-123\n\nFlow (Manager's Spec v2 - JS Backend creates run):\n1. POST /runs/start → starts existing run (created by JS Backend)\n2. Poll GET /status until \"awaiting_confirmation\"\n3. GET /competitors → review competitor list\n4. POST /runs/competitors/confirm → triggers Stage 2-4 (run_id in body)\n5. Poll GET /status until \"completed\"\n6. GET /result → allocation results",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Check if server is running.\n\n**No authentication required.**\n\n**Expected Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-19T...\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\"\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /ready",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/ready",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["ready"]
            },
            "description": "Check if server AND database are ready.\n\n**Expected Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ready\",\n  \"checks\": {\n    \"database\": true\n  }\n}\n```"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Run Management",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Start Existing Run (v2 - Manager Spec)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"run_id\": 1,\n  \"action\": \"start\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/start",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "start"]
            },
            "description": "**Manager's Spec v2**\n\nStart an existing run (created by JS Backend).\n\n**Change run_id in body to your actual run ID**\n\n**Response:**\n- run_id: The run ID\n- status: 'started' or 'error'\n- error_message: null or error details"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Create New Run",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"customer_name\": \"BMW Group\",\n  \"industry\": \"Automotive\",\n  \"brand_kpi\": \"adaware\",\n  \"media_channels\": [\"TV\", \"ONLINE\", \"SOCIAL\"],\n  \"goal_direction\": \"budget_to_impact\",\n  \"goal_text\": \"I have 4 million euros for Q3 brand awareness campaign\",\n  \"total_budget\": 4000000\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new budget allocation request.\n\n**Required Headers:**\n- X-Session-Token: Your session identifier\n\n**Body Fields:**\n- customer_name: Company name\n- industry: Business sector\n- brand_kpi: adaware | aided | consider\n- media_channels: Array of channels\n- goal_direction: budget_to_impact | goal_to_budget\n- goal_text: Description of your goal\n- total_budget: Amount in EUR\n\n**IMPORTANT:** Note the 'id' in response - use it for all other requests!"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Run Status (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/status",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "status"]
            },
            "description": "Check the status of your run.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Status Values:**\n- pending: Waiting to start\n- matching: Finding competitors\n- awaiting_confirmation: Need to approve competitors\n- generating: AI is working\n- completed: Done!\n- failed: Error occurred\n- cancelled: User stopped it"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Stop Run (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reason\": \"User cancelled the request\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/stop",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "stop"]
            },
            "description": "Cancel a running or queued request.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Process Run (run_id=1) - MOCK (hardcoded)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/process",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "process"]
            },
            "description": "**MOCK - Uses hardcoded values (no AI)**\n\nThis endpoint manually processes a run with FAKE data.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Returns fixed allocation:**\n- TV: 37%\n- Online: 28%\n- Social: 22%\n- OOH: 13%\n\n**Use /process-ai instead for REAL AI!**"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Process Run with REAL AI (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/process-ai",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "process-ai"]
            },
            "description": "**REAL AI - Calls OpenAI GPT-4o!**\n\nThis endpoint triggers the REAL AI pipeline:\n1. Assembles prompt with expert knowledge\n2. Calls OpenAI GPT-4o\n3. Parses and validates response\n4. Generates intelligent feedback\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Response time:** 5-15 seconds\n\n**Response includes:**\n- ai_powered: true\n- model: gpt-4o-2024-08-06\n- tokens_used: actual token count\n- latency_ms: API response time\n- confidence: AI's confidence (0-1)\n- allocation_summary: AI-generated allocation\n\n**Note:** Requires valid OPENAI_API_KEY in .env"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Competitors",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Confirm Competitors v2 - APPROVE (Manager Spec)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"run_id\": 1,\n  \"action\": \"approved\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/competitors/confirm",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "competitors", "confirm"]
            },
            "description": "**Manager's Spec v2**\n\nApprove competitors with run_id in body (not URL).\n\n**Change run_id in body to your actual run ID**\n\nAccepts both 'approve' and 'approved' action values.\nUses all competitors from Stage 1 (no selected_competitors param)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Confirm Competitors v2 - CANCEL (Manager Spec)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"run_id\": 1,\n  \"action\": \"cancel\",\n  \"reason\": \"Competitors not suitable\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/competitors/confirm",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "competitors", "confirm"]
            },
            "description": "**Manager's Spec v2**\n\nCancel the run with run_id in body (not URL).\n\n**Change run_id in body to your actual run ID**"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Competitors (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/competitors",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "competitors"]
            },
            "description": "Get the list of matched competitor brands.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\nShows which brands the AI will analyze."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Confirm Competitors - APPROVE (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"approve\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/competitors/confirm",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "competitors", "confirm"]
            },
            "description": "Approve the competitor list and continue.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Actions:**\n- approve: Continue with these competitors\n- cancel: Reject and stop the run"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Confirm Competitors - CANCEL (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"cancel\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/competitors/confirm",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "competitors", "confirm"]
            },
            "description": "Reject competitors and cancel the run.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Feasibility Check (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/feasibility",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "feasibility"]
            },
            "description": "Check if we have enough data to generate recommendations.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Response:**\n- is_feasible: true/false\n- warnings: Issues to be aware of\n- suggestions: Alternatives if not feasible"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Results (THE OUTPUT!)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Allocation Result (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/result",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "result"]
            },
            "description": "**THE MAIN OUTPUT!**\n\nGet the budget allocation recommendation.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Response includes:**\n- allocations: Channel breakdown (TV 37%, Online 28%, etc.)\n- total_budget_eur: Total budget\n- reasoning_summary: Why this allocation\n- confidence_score: How confident the AI is"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Chat / Feedback Cards (run_id=1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/chat",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "chat"]
            },
            "description": "Get feedback cards (warnings, alerts, recommendations).\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Message Types:**\n- summary: General summary\n- warning (yellow): Something to note\n- alert (red): Important issue\n- recommendation: Suggestion"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Owner Only (Traces)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Trace - As USER (Should FAIL 403)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-User-Role",
                "value": "user"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/trace",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "trace"]
            },
            "description": "**This should FAIL with 403!**\n\nRegular users cannot access prompt traces.\n\nExpected: {\"detail\": \"Owner access required\"}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Trace - As OWNER (Should SUCCEED)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "X-Session-Token",
                "value": "my-test-session-123"
              },
              {
                "key": "X-User-Role",
                "value": "owner"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8002/api/v1/runs/1/trace",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": ["localhost"],
              "port": "8002",
              "path": ["api", "v1", "runs", "1", "trace"]
            },
            "description": "**Owner only!**\n\nSee exactly what was sent to GPT-4o.\n\n**Change the '1' in URL to your run_id**\n\n**Response includes:**\n- prompt: What we sent to the AI\n- response: What the AI replied\n- tokens: Usage count\n- latency_ms: How long it took"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
